  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level is set to 3. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are assessed; the 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' because the assessment team judged that boundary-condition equivalency between the bench-top validation experiment and the clinical COU is self-evident from the shared pump geometry, and therefore concluded that a formal equivalency evaluation 'does not apply to this COU.' No factorStatus 'not-applicable' encoding was applied, leaving a material epistemic gap at MRL 3. Decision recorded as Accepted.",
