      "rationale": "An independent CFD engineer reviewed boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection, and hemolysis post-processing scripts. No errors were identified. Use error factor is satisfied at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence and hemolysis sub-models must be justified through literature evidence and sensitivity analysis for the operating regime.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on prior pump literature. The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model is acknowledged to have significant uncertainty at low shear exposures. A model-form sensitivity study was performed but showed up to 30% variation in predicted MIH across plausible model alternatives. Achieved level is below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary condition inputs must be characterized with documented uncertainty bounds and propagated through Monte Carlo analysis.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and inlet velocity profiles were characterized with uncertainty bounds from literature. Monte Carlo propagation (n=500) was performed. 95th-percentile hemolysis index predictions remain below the clinical threshold. Achieved level meets required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use a sufficient number of independent test samples to characterize experimental variability, with statistical summary reported.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis measurements were taken from n=4 independent pump runs per operating point. Statistical variability is reported as mean ± SD, but the sample size is below the n=6 threshold typically cited for Gradation 3. Achieved level is below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal demonstration that boundary condition inputs used in the validation model are equivalent to those in the COU model, including inlet velocity profiles, outlet pressure conditions, and rotational speed tolerances.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this context of use because the validation and COU models share the same pump geometry and are driven by the same nominal operating-point specifications. The team judged that boundary-condition equivalency is self-evident from the shared geometry and operating envelope, and therefore no formal equivalency evaluation was conducted. The factor was left as not-assessed rather than encoded as not-applicable, representing an epistemic gap at Model Risk Level 3 where a formal equivalency argument would materially strengthen credibility."
    }
