    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Seven of twelve assessed credibility factors meet their required levels; five fall one gradation below required. The assessment team determined that the shortfalls are mitigated by the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, which demonstrates that 95th-percentile hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold across all operating points. The equivalency of input parameters factor was not assessed on the basis that the shared pump geometry renders a formal evaluation unnecessary. The package is accepted at Low assurance level pending supplementary experimental data to close the open gaps.",
